---
import logo from "../assets/logo.svg";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Clash for AI Docs</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Documentation for Clash for AI, a local desktop gateway for switching AI relay providers behind one stable endpoint."
    />
    <style>
      :root {
        --bg: #f6f1e8;
        --panel: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72);
        --text: #1f1a17;
        --muted: #66584f;
        --line: rgba(74, 57, 44, 0.14);
        --accent: #bb4d2f;
        --accent-strong: #8b311b;
        --shadow: 0 24px 60px rgba(60, 32, 15, 0.12);
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--text);
        font-family:
          "Fraunces",
          "Iowan Old Style",
          "Palatino Linotype",
          Georgia,
          serif;
        background:
          radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(255, 210, 178, 0.65), transparent 28%),
          radial-gradient(circle at bottom right, rgba(221, 137, 96, 0.2), transparent 26%),
          linear-gradient(180deg, #fbf7f1 0%, var(--bg) 100%);
      }

      a {
        color: inherit;
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      .shell {
        width: min(1120px, calc(100vw - 40px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 32px 0 64px;
      }

      .topbar {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 16px;
        margin-bottom: 48px;
      }

      .brand {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 14px;
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .brand img {
        width: 36px;
        height: 36px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        box-shadow: 0 10px 24px rgba(92, 44, 25, 0.15);
      }

      .topbar nav {
        display: flex;
        gap: 20px;
        font-size: 15px;
        color: var(--muted);
      }

      .hero {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(320px, 0.9fr);
        gap: 28px;
        align-items: stretch;
      }

      .hero-copy,
      .hero-card,
      .section-card {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        background: var(--panel);
        backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      }

      .hero-copy {
        border-radius: 34px;
        padding: 40px;
      }

      .eyebrow {
        margin: 0 0 16px;
        font-size: 12px;
        letter-spacing: 0.18em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--accent);
      }

      h1 {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: clamp(48px, 8vw, 86px);
        line-height: 0.95;
        letter-spacing: -0.05em;
      }

      .hero-copy p {
        margin: 18px 0 0;
        max-width: 52ch;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--muted);
      }

      .actions {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 14px;
        margin-top: 28px;
      }

      .button {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        min-height: 46px;
        padding: 0 18px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.02em;
      }

      .button.primary {
        background: var(--accent);
        color: #fff7f2;
      }

      .button.primary:hover {
        background: var(--accent-strong);
      }

      .button.secondary {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        color: var(--text);
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.48);
      }

      .hero-card {
        border-radius: 30px;
        padding: 28px;
        display: grid;
        gap: 18px;
      }

      .hero-card h2 {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 18px;
      }

      .hero-card ol {
        margin: 0;
        padding-left: 22px;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.75;
      }

      .section-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
        gap: 18px;
        margin-top: 22px;
      }

      .section-card {
        border-radius: 24px;
        padding: 24px;
      }

      .section-card h3 {
        margin: 0 0 10px;
        font-size: 20px;
      }

      .section-card p {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.7;
      }

      .section-card a {
        display: inline-flex;
        margin-top: 18px;
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--accent-strong);
      }

      .section-title {
        margin: 42px 0 0;
        font-size: 32px;
      }

      .section-lead {
        margin: 12px 0 0;
        max-width: 64ch;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.8;
      }

      @media (max-width: 960px) {
        .hero {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .section-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .topbar {
          flex-direction: column;
          align-items: flex-start;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="shell">
      <header class="topbar">
        <a class="brand" href="/">
          <img src={logo.src} alt="Clash for AI" />
          <span>Clash for AI Docs</span>
        </a>
        <nav>
          <a href="/introduction/">Introduction</a>
          <a href="/quick-start/">Quick Start</a>
          <a href="/tool-integration/">Integration</a>
          <a href="/providers/">Providers</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/xiaoyuandev/clash-for-ai">GitHub</a>
        </nav>
      </header>

      <section class="hero">
        <article class="hero-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Local Desktop Gateway</p>
          <h1>Switch relay providers without rewriting every tool config.</h1>
          <p>
            Clash for AI gives coding tools, chat clients, and SDK workflows one stable local
            endpoint. The desktop app manages upstream providers, health checks, and request logs in
            one place.
          </p>
          <div class="actions">
            <a class="button primary" href="/quick-start/">Start with Quick Start</a>
            <a class="button secondary" href="/introduction/">Read the Product Overview</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <aside class="hero-card">
          <h2>What this docs site covers</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>How to launch Clash for AI and connect your first tool</li>
            <li>How OpenAI-compatible relay providers should be configured</li>
            <li>Why `/v1`, model discovery, and fallback behavior matter</li>
            <li>How to avoid common setup mistakes with coding tools and chat clients</li>
          </ol>
        </aside>
      </section>

      <h2 class="section-title">Start here</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">
        The first version of the docs is intentionally focused: setup, provider compatibility,
        practical integration, and operational FAQs. That gives you a clean structure for expanding
        into screenshots, walkthroughs, and troubleshooting later.
      </p>

      <section class="section-grid">
        <article class="section-card">
          <h3>Introduction</h3>
          <p>Understand the local gateway model, provider switching workflow, and current scope.</p>
          <a href="/introduction/">Read overview</a>
        </article>
        <article class="section-card">
          <h3>Quick Start</h3>
          <p>Launch the app, add a provider, and connect a tool using one stable local endpoint.</p>
          <a href="/quick-start/">Open quick start</a>
        </article>
        <article class="section-card">
          <h3>Tool Integration</h3>
          <p>See the setup pattern for coding tools, desktop clients, and OpenAI SDK based scripts.</p>
          <a href="/tool-integration/">Browse integrations</a>
        </article>
        <article class="section-card">
          <h3>Providers</h3>
          <p>Read the `/v1` guidance, model list behavior, and compatibility notes for relay APIs.</p>
          <a href="/providers/">Read provider notes</a>
        </article>
        <article class="section-card">
          <h3>FAQ</h3>
          <p>Find answers about fallback behavior, model selection responsibility, and protocol limits.</p>
          <a href="/faq/">Open FAQ</a>
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
